            </div>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div id="cooling-section" class="hidden">
        <div class="step">
            <h2>Step 1: Category III Codes</h2>
            <p>Scalp cooling is often billed under "Emerging Technology" codes. Ensure your provider uses:</p>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>0662T:</strong> Scalp cooling device initial measurement and calibration.</li>
                <li><strong>0663T:</strong> Scalp cooling device placement, monitoring, and removal (per treatment).</li>
            </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="step">
            <h2>Step 2: Scalp Cooling Script</h2>
            <div class="script-box">
                "Does my plan cover <strong>Category III CPT codes 0662T and 0663T</strong> for scalp cooling during chemotherapy? If it is currently excluded, can I request a <strong>clinical exception</strong> due to the medical necessity of hair preservation for my mental and physical recovery?"
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="step">
        <h2>Estimate Your Responsibility</h2>
        <div class="input-group">
            <label>Estimated Total Service Cost ($)</label>
            <input type="number" id="cost" placeholder="e.g., 2500">
        </div>
        <div class="input-group">
            <label>Remaining Annual Deductible ($)</label>
            <input type="number" id="deductible" placeholder="0">
        </div>
        <div class="input-group">
            <label>Your Coinsurance % (e.g., 20)</label>
            <input type="number" id="coinsurance" placeholder="20">
        </div>
        <button onclick="calculateCost()">Generate Estimate</button>

        <div id="resultBox" class="calc-box" style="display:none;">
            <h3>Your Financial Roadmap:</h3>
            <p>Applied to Deductible: <span id="resDeductible">$0</span></p>
